  "response_text": "A young woman with long curly brown hair, small earrings, and a purple top faces forward against a vivid textured background of magenta, purple, blue, and green. She smiles warmly at first, then her expression softens into a more neutral look. A visual effect appears over her face: a pale, cracked, mask-like layer covers her skin, with pieces breaking and flaking away across her cheeks, nose, forehead, and chin. The effect makes her face look dry and peeling, with loose fragments scattered down toward her neck.\n\nThe view changes to the product packaging. A large white bottle fills the screen at an angle, showing a bright, blocky label with a purple top band reading “PROPA” and oversized purple letters “pH” over bands of blue, green, and orange. Two Propa pH bottles are then displayed side by side against the same colorful purple background. Both labels read “astringent cleanser,” with smaller text indicating “acne medication & moisturizer.” The bottle on the left is tinted purple and the one on the right is a pale gray bottle with a blue cap. Small on-screen text along the bottom reads, “Use as directed.”\n\nThe young woman returns against the purple backdrop, now with a smooth white oval covering her whole face like a clean, blank mask. The white layer begins to break apart and slide away in small flakes, revealing her natural face underneath. As the pieces clear, her eyes and mouth reappear, and she looks forward with a calm, slightly open-mouthed expression. The last bits of the white layer disappear from her forehead, leaving her face fully visible and clear. She smiles again, looking relaxed and confident. She raises one hand and gently presses her palm to her cheek, then tilts her head into her hand while smiling broadly.\n\nThe commercial ends with a product lineup on a flat surface against the same colorful textured purple background. Three Propa pH products stand upright: a small rectangular box on the left labeled as a gelled acne medication, a larger center bottle labeled “astringent cleanser” with a blue cap, and a white bottle on the right labeled “foaming face wash” with an orange cap. All three packages use the same bold Propa pH logo with purple lettering and bright blue, green, and orange color blocks.",
